How To Run The Program:
----------------------------
1. Use the Command [Ctrl + T ] to open the terminal
2. Use the Command [make] to compile the driver_*.c files and get the executable objects
3. Use the Command [sudo insmod driver_*.ko] to define and insert the driver moduler.
4. Use the Command [lsmod] to check whether the module has been inserted or not.
5. Use the Command [make app] to compile userapp
6. User the Command [sudo ./userapp ] to test the program
7. Use the Command [sudo rmmod driver_*.ko] to remove the driver.
8. During the process, you can also use the Command[dmesg] to check the kernel message
9. The Function of the char_driver contains: Read, Write, Lseek, Icotl, Release and Clean
